designing for voice

00:03:12.670 --> 00:03:15.530
is different-- different than
for mobile and for websites.

00:03:18.140 --> 00:03:20.650
Please, take that at face value.

00:03:20.650 --> 00:03:24.490
I'm making no claims
about complexity here.

00:03:24.490 --> 00:03:27.647
Designing can be a tough thing.

00:03:27.647 --> 00:03:28.480
It's just different.

00:03:28.480 --> 00:03:29.870
Voice is different.

00:03:29.870 --> 00:03:33.680
And that's what I'm hoping to
unpack a bit for you today.

00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:35.920
So here's a quick look at
what we're going to cover.

00:03:35.920 --> 00:03:38.110
I want to cover off
the value of voice--

00:03:38.110 --> 00:03:40.780
again, voice online, no screens.

00:03:40.780 --> 00:03:42.640
We'll cover some
considerations, things

00:03:42.640 --> 00:03:44.590
that you should be
thinking about as you're

00:03:44.590 --> 00:03:47.110
creating voice experiences.

00:03:47.110 --> 00:03:50.690
And some opportunities-- really
some ideas around use cases.

00:03:50.690 --> 00:03:51.190
All right?

00:03:51.190 --> 00:03:52.860
Sounds good?

00:03:52.860 --> 00:03:54.770
Good.

00:03:54.770 --> 00:03:58.420
So let's start with
the value of voice.

00:03:58.420 --> 00:04:00.140
The question here
really is, why?

00:04:00.140 --> 00:04:01.310
Why voice?

00:04:01.310 --> 00:04:05.000
And for me, it boils
down to three things--

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:08.390
speed, simplicity, and ubiquity.

00:04:08.390 --> 00:04:09.330
All right.

00:04:09.330 --> 00:04:11.580
Now let's start with speed.

00:04:11.580 --> 00:04:15.710
Now voice interactions can
be extremely, extremely fast.

00:04:15.710 --> 00:04:18.320
Done well, they're even faster
than pulling your mobile phone

00:04:18.320 --> 00:04:20.399
out of your back pocket.

00:04:20.399 --> 00:04:26.870
It's like, getting to the app
you want on a mobile phone

00:04:26.870 --> 00:04:29.930
takes a tap or two,
maybe even a swipe.

00:04:29.930 --> 00:04:31.640
And when you get
to the app, you're

00:04:31.640 --> 00:04:36.890
another tap and maybe even
some typing away from a result.

00:04:36.890 --> 00:04:39.540
With voice, you get
to bundle all that.

00:04:39.540 --> 00:04:41.780
And it's like the
ultimate shortcut.

00:04:41.780 --> 00:04:44.360
That's what I think
is really cool.

00:04:44.360 --> 00:04:47.120
Then there's just the
simplicity of use.

00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:50.480
You have users who
already know what to do.

00:04:50.480 --> 00:04:51.230
This is language.

00:04:51.230 --> 00:04:52.520
It's conversation.

00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:54.260
And they've been
doing this forever--

00:04:54.260 --> 00:04:56.570
well, since they were born.

00:04:56.570 --> 00:05:00.500
And there's really
nothing for them to learn.

00:05:00.500 --> 00:05:02.570
Don't get me wrong, I'm
the first to acknowledge

00:05:02.570 --> 00:05:05.360
the challenges around design
and technologies and things

00:05:05.360 --> 00:05:06.270
like that.

00:05:06.270 --> 00:05:08.950
But the promise here
is, say what you want,

00:05:08.950 --> 00:05:09.920
get what you want.

00:05:09.920 --> 00:05:13.410
And it doesn't really get
much simpler than that.

00:05:13.410 --> 00:05:17.810
And finally, there's just the
sheer number of entry points--

00:05:17.810 --> 00:05:20.090
a number that continues to grow.

00:05:20.090 --> 00:05:22.880
You can already reach Google
Assistant and our actions

00:05:22.880 --> 00:05:26.960
on Google partners on
millions of devices.

00:05:26.960 --> 00:05:29.870
And it feels like there are new
surfaces and new opportunities

00:05:29.870 --> 00:05:32.060
popping up all the time.

00:05:32.060 --> 00:05:36.247
All you need really is a
microphone and a speaker.

00:05:36.247 --> 00:05:38.330
Well, that and a network
connection to the actions

00:05:38.330 --> 00:05:40.650
on Google Platform,
but you get the point.

00:05:40.650 --> 00:05:43.950
The reality here is that
the numbers are significant.

00:05:43.950 --> 00:05:46.580
The potential here is massive.

00:05:46.580 --> 00:05:49.260
By the way, I don't
know if anybody

00:05:49.260 --> 00:05:53.000
saw this thing that was
launched a couple weeks ago.

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:57.140
Literally, cardboard, a
microphone, and a speaker,

00:05:57.140 --> 00:05:59.810
Raspberry Pi, and you're
connected to Assistant.

00:05:59.810 --> 00:06:01.070
That's really cool stuff.

00:06:01.070 --> 00:06:03.240
Did anyone get one?

00:06:03.240 --> 00:06:04.180
No?

00:06:04.180 --> 00:06:06.170
Oh, one guy.

00:06:06.170 --> 00:06:07.970
Get one.

00:06:07.970 --> 00:06:09.810
I have one sitting
